'''''Phidippus pulcherrimus''''' is a species of spider in the [[Salticidae]] (jumping spider) family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catalogueoflife.org/col/details/species/id/7893275|title=Phidippus pulcherrimus|work=[[Catalogue of Life]]|accessdate=April 26, 2014}}</ref>  It belongs to the genus ''[[Phidippus]]'' and is found in the [[United States]].

''P. pulcheriimus'' was first described in 1885 by [[Eugen von Keyserling]].

